{"id":1681265,"retrievedAt":"2026-04-26T11:59:29.266Z","response":{"adult":false,"backdrop_path":null,"belongs_to_collection":null,"budget":0,"genres":[{"id":18,"name":"Drama"},{"id":10749,"name":"Romance"},{"id":10770,"name":"TV Movie"}],"homepage":"","id":1681265,"imdb_id":null,"origin_country":["KR"],"original_language":"ko","original_title":"폴라로이드","overview":"Deok-jung, a taxi driver who speaks of death as casually as small talk, receives a terminal diagnosis. He buys a worn-out coffee vending machine — a mirror of himself — and sets out to find meaning in whatever time he has left. At a cheap lodging house, he crosses paths with Jeong-suk, a down-on-her-luck karaoke hostess past her prime. Moved by something he can't quite name, he offers her a deal: look after the machine, and he'll call it a relationship. Bound together by hardship and loneliness, the two begin to quietly tend to each other's wounds, and what started as a contract slowly becomes something neither expected. Before he goes, Deok-jung leaves Jeong-suk the vending machine as his final bequest — and in that rusted, weathered thing, she finds a reason to begin again.","popularity":0.05,"poster_path":"/z10Y4KYOk4INULWDUBDjrYqZxvf.jpg","production_companies":[],"production_countries":[{"iso_3166_1":"KR","name":"South Korea"}],"release_date":"2026-05-04","revenue":0,"runtime":101,"softcore":false,"spoken_languages":[{"english_name":"Korean","iso_639_1":"ko","name":"한국어/조선말"}],"status":"Released","tagline":"\"Like a photograph taken of someone you knew you were about to lose.\"","title":"Polaroid","video":false,"vote_average":0,"vote_count":0,"alternative_titles":{"titles":[]},"credits":{"cast":[{"adult":false,"gender":2,"id":79574,"known_for_department":"Acting","name":"Park Won-sang","original_name":"박원상","popularity":1.3901,"profile_path":"/1BUaoK9hmgayqrXUzbRezKLoyZQ.jpg","cast_id":3,"character":"","credit_id":"69eccc0b915dce524a17d108","order":0},{"adult":false,"gender":1,"id":994300,"known_for_d